text:
#War economics...
‚≠ê Actors were signed two years ago at then prevalent rates.
‚≠ê CoP [‚Çπ 150 cr] includes all fees/remuneration.
‚≠ê Hrithik has a backend deal. He's a partner in profits.
‚≠ê #War will be a franchise like #MissionImpossible series, with Hrithik staying constant.

name: taran adarsh
text: 2019 has been a fantastic year for #Bollywood and the super success of #War reiterates the fact that *well made* biggies - targeted at PAN India audience - will always be embraced warmly by the paying public... Expecting #YRF to green light #War2 soon.

name: taran adarsh
text: Also, they pave way for mid-range and metro-centric films, in the process... The biggies cultivate / foster the cinema-going habit, which is pivotal these days, since the digital medium is strengthening its roots in India. #War

name: taran adarsh
text: Tent pole / event / big ticket films are a must... They get the numbers... They drive the audience [in hordes] to movie halls... They contribute to ticket sales and footfalls... They infuse confidence in the financial sector. #War
